# Nexora: System Architecture & Product Design Document

Nexora is an AI-powered career guidance and mentorship platform for college students designed to bridge the gap between academic education and industry readiness. Rather than offering a simple Q&A chatbot interface, Nexora uses a hybrid system combining conversational profiling, short adaptive assessments, structured dynamic roadmaps, and mentor matching.

---

## 1. Complete System Architecture

Nexora utilizes a **Modular Monolith** architecture for the MVP to ensure high velocity, transitioning to a distributed, event-driven microservices pattern as the user base scales.

### System Components & Data Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Clients
    Client[Next.js Web Client] <--> |HTTPS / WSS| Gateway[API Gateway / BFF]
    
    %% Gateway to Core Services
    Gateway <--> ProfileSvc[Profile & Auth Service]
    Gateway <--> ChatSvc[Conversational Profiler Service]
    Gateway <--> AssessSvc[Adaptive Assessment Engine]
    Gateway <--> RoadmapSvc[Roadmap Generation Service]
    Gateway <--> MentorSvc[Mentorship & Match Service]

    %% External APIs & Integrations
    ChatSvc <--> |Structured Outputs| LLM[Gemini 1.5 / 2.0 Flash API]
    RoadmapSvc <--> LLM
    RoadmapSvc --> |Async Job Queue| RedisQueue[BullMQ / Redis Cache]
    
    %% Databases
    ProfileSvc <--> DB[(PostgreSQL)]
    AssessSvc <--> DB
    RoadmapSvc <--> DB
    MentorSvc <--> DB
    MentorSvc <--> VectorDB[(pgvector / Vector Search)]
    
    %% Caching & Storage
    RoadmapSvc --> CDN[Cloudflare CDN / Static Assets]
```

### Key Modules
1. **API Gateway / BFF (Backend-For-Frontend)**: Handles authentication, session management, request routing, and rate limiting.
2. **Conversational Profiler**: Tracks user onboarding chat sessions, parses key inputs (using structured JSON schemas via LLM Function Calling), and stores raw responses.
3. **Adaptive Assessment Engine**: Dynamically fetches assessment questions from the question bank based on estimated student ability ($\theta$) and the classified career path.
4. **Roadmap Generation Service**: Takes scoring vectors, timeline variables, and weekly commitment data to compose a structured JSON roadmap.
5. **Mentorship & Match Service**: Ranks mentors based on cosine similarity of user skill gaps and mentor domain expertise.

